Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Enyobeni tavern owner and two employees have been arrested. The owner (52) was arrested for selling liquor to minors. WATCH:Â Mass funeral for Enyobeni tavern victims "After the opening of the case by Liquor Board, the investigators embarked on the investigation process which resulted to fines to the amount of R2,000 being issued to each of the two tavern employees, whilst summons were served to the owner for his immediate arrest and appearance in the court of law," a statement by the office of the Eastern Cape Provincial Police Commissioner read. Authorities are investigating what could have led to the deaths of the 21 teens.